.TH heightpipe 1 "February 2026" "arma-tools" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
heightpipe \- upscale/correct/erode heightmaps with deterministic multi-scale pipeline
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B heightpipe
.I input.rawf32 output.rawf32
.B --in-width
.I N
.B --in-height
.I N
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B heightpipe
reads a headerless row-major float32 heightmap, upscales by 2/4/8/16,
applies scale-aware correction modes, runs stepped erosion, and writes
a headerless row-major float32 output.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI "--scale " 2|4|8|16
Upscale factor (default 2).
.TP
.BI "--resample " bicubic|lanczos3
Upscale kernel (default bicubic).
.TP
.BI "--correction " mode
Correction mode:
.B preset
(default),
.B none,
.B unsharp,
.B curv_gain,
.B residual,
.B guided_sharp,
.B hybrid,
.B terrain_16x
(alias for preset chain).
.TP
.BI "--preset " name
Preset chain for
.B --correction preset
:
.B none,
.B sharp,
.B retain_detail,
.BR terrain_16x .
.TP
.BI "--macro " 0|1
Enable macro erosion pass (default 1).
.TP
.BI "--meso " 0|1
Enable meso erosion pass (default 1).
.TP
.BI "--micro " 0|1
Enable micro erosion pass (default 1).
.TP
.BI "--seed " N
Deterministic RNG seed (default 1).
.TP
.BI "--dump " slope.raw curvature.raw flow.raw
Write diagnostics as raw float32 maps at output resolution.
.TP
.BR -h , " --help"
Show help.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR wrp_heightmap (1)
